==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Cratch
<hw>Cratch</hw> <pr>(kr?ch; 224)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[OE.
<ets>cracche</ets>, <ets>crecche</ets>, F. <ets>cr⟦egrave⟧che</ets>
crib, manger, fr. OHG. <ets>krippa</ets>, <ets>krippea</ets>, G.
<ets>krippe</ets> crib. See <er>Crib</er>.]</ety> <def>A manger or open
frame for hay; a crib; a rack.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Begin from first where He encradled was,⟦br⟧
In simple <qex>cratch</qex>, wrapt in a wad of hay.</q>
<rj><qau>Spenser.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Cratch cradle</b></col>, <cd>a representation of the
figure of the cratch, made upon the fingers with a string; cat's cradle;
-- called also <altname>scratch cradle</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Crate</ent>⟦br⟧
